author: hwright
msg: On the explore-wc branch:
With apologies to Erik Hülsmann, rip out working copy propcaching.  WC-NG
does not record this information, so the rest of the working copy library
should not depending on it existing.
This reduces the number of test failures to 529.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/props.c
(svn_wc__load_props, svn_wc__install_props, svn_wc__hash_props,
svn_wc_props_modified_p): Don't depend on prop caching in an entry.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/lock.c
(introduce_propcaching): Remove.
(maybe_upgrade_format): Don't introduce propcaching when upgrading.

author: cmpilato
msg: Fix some error leakage.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/commit.c
(checkout_dir, checkout_file, proppatch_resource): Tweak error
handling to avoid unnecessary (and often incorrect) work.
NOTE: This change was originally made on the 'http-protocol-v2'
branch, but has been merged here *without mergeinfo* to simplify the
reintegration of that branch later.  We'll use 'svn merge
--record-only' on that branch to block the reverse merge of this
change there.  Life is easy.  Life is grand.
